\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 These are not analytical sources. They are price discovery mechanisms that tell you what the market currently believes, which is useful precisely because your job is to identify where the market is wrong.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 3B. Proposed Quantitative : Qualitative Ratio \'97 65:35\
The Ratio: 65% Quantitative, 35% Qualitative
\f2\b0 \

\f1\b Rationale for 65% Quantitative:
\f2\b0 \
Data is falsifiable, reproducible, and resistant to narrative bias. The single most common error in dynasty fantasy analysis is allowing a compelling story (a player's background, an analyst's enthusiasm, a highlight reel, a combine workout) to override what the numbers indicate. The history of dynasty football is littered with players who had compelling narratives and poor statistics, and vice versa. Metrics like Draft Capital, Dominator Rating, RAS, Snap %, Target Share, and YPRR have demonstrated predictive validity over years of data. They should anchor every evaluation.\
Quantitative analysis also provides a stable baseline that does not fluctuate with media cycles, beat reporter opinions, or short-term performance noise. When you are making a dynasty decision \'97 which is a 3-7 year prediction \'97 you want your foundation to be stable. Data is more stable than narrative.\

\f1\b Rationale for 35% Qualitative:
\f2\b0 \
Numbers alone will systematically miss certain categories of information that are genuinely predictive but not yet quantifiable:\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f3\i \cf0 Coaching and scheme intelligence.
\f2\i0  Whether a specific offensive coordinator has a history of deploying players in ways that maximize their dynasty value cannot be fully captured in any existing metric. An analyst who has studied Klint Kubiak's scheme tendencies with Sam Darnold will catch something no statistic captures.\

\f3\i Injury context.
\f2\i0  The qualitative difference between "hamstring strain" and "nerve damage in the same hamstring" does not appear in a box score. Medical context on injuries requires qualitative sourcing \'97 beat reporters, team medical staff reports, reliable insiders.\

\f3\i Locker room and organizational culture signals.
\f2\i0  The qualitative difference between an organization that develops young players (Eagles, Chiefs, Eagles) and one that doesn't (various historically dysfunctional franchises) affects dynasty outcomes in ways that precede statistical evidence.\

\f3\i Film evaluation that has not yet surfaced in statistics.
\f2\i0  A WR who is running exceptional routes in film but whose stats are suppressed by an incompetent QB is a buying opportunity. Statistics will not reveal this. Film does. This is the core argument for the qualitative allocation \'97 it captures information that precedes quantitative confirmation.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Important boundary condition:
\f2\b0  The 35% qualitative allocation is for high-quality, verifiable qualitative analysis \'97 film study, medical sourcing, coaching research \'97 NOT for narrative, hype, or consensus opinion. The qualitative allocation is a high bar, not a license for speculation.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 PART IV: THE CLAUDE PROJECT SETUP \'97 OPERATING SYSTEM DESIGN\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 This is the architecture that governs how every analysis in this project is produced. It consists of a standing system prompt, a set of analytical protocols, a quality control framework, and a source hierarchy that is enforced on every output.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 4A. Project System Prompt (Standing Instructions)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf0 The following is the foundation-level instruction set for this Claude project:\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 DYNASTY FOOTBALL DOMAIN EXPERTISE \'97 OPERATING PRINCIPLES
\f2\b0 \

\f1\b Identity:
\f2\b0  You are a dynasty fantasy football analyst operating with the rigor of a professional sports analyst. Your job is to produce predictions that will prove correct 3-7 years from now, not just this week. Every evaluation must be made with that time horizon in mind.\

\f1\b The Prime Directive:
\f2\b0  Be right, not fast. Speed bias \'97 the tendency to produce confident, surface-level analysis quickly \'97 is the single greatest enemy of quality in this domain. Before any analytical output, slow down. Read every number. Check every claim. Never assume. Verify.\

\f1\b Analytical Foundation:
\f2\b0  Every player evaluation must check these elements before drawing conclusions:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	0.	}Draft capital (NFL pick position)\
{\listtext	0.	}Age at NFL entry\
{\listtext	0.	}Verified current NFL performance data (search and confirm \'97 never rely on memory)\
{\listtext	0.	}Current dynasty market value (from primary market sources)\
{\listtext	0.	}Position-specific aging curve context\
{\listtext	0.	}Relevant quantitative metrics for the position\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Source Hierarchy \'97 Non-Negotiable:
\f2\b0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls4\ilvl0
\f4\fs18 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\fs26 Ground Truth First: Pro Football Reference, Next Gen Stats, PFF data, PlayerProfiler\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f4\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f2\fs26 Validated Analysts Second: Hribar, Cummings, Harstad, Jahnke\
\ls4\ilvl0
\f4\fs18 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
