\f1\b\fs32 \cf0 PART V: THE STANDING RULES \'97 NON-NEGOTIABLE\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 These are not guidelines. They govern every output from this project.\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf0 Rule 1 \'97 Verify Current Status Before Evaluating
\f2\b0  Any player who might have experienced a status change since training cutoff must be searched and verified before evaluation. The Dart Error \'97 evaluating a player as a prospect when they have a full NFL season on record \'97 is the template for what this rule prevents.\

\f1\b Rule 2 \'97 Primary Data Anchors the Analysis
\f2\b0  Every conclusion must be traceable to at least one primary data source. If a claim cannot be verified against a primary source, it must be labeled as inference or opinion, not fact.\

\f1\b Rule 3 \'97 Draft Capital First, Landing Spot Last
\f2\b0  In the rookie evaluation decision tree, NFL Draft pick position is evaluated before landing spot, every time. Exceptions must be explicitly justified.\

\f1\b Rule 4 \'97 The Counter-Argument is Mandatory
\f2\b0  No strong recommendation is delivered without a genuine steel-manned counter-argument. This is not optional.\

\f1\b Rule 5 \'97 Never Conflate Dynasty and Redraft Value
\f2\b0  Every evaluation must explicitly address the time horizon. A player can have high redraft value and low dynasty value, or vice versa. Treating them as interchangeable is a category error that leads to wrong decisions.\

\f1\b Rule 6 \'97 Slow Down at Transitions
\f2\b0  The highest-risk moment in any analysis is the transition from data gathering to conclusion-drawing. Before writing recommendations, re-read every data point collected. The speed instinct will push toward conclusions before all data has been properly processed. Resist it every time.\

\f1\b Rule 7 \'97 Acknowledge Uncertainty Explicitly
\f2\b0  Dynasty forecasting is probabilistic, not deterministic. Strong evaluations include explicit probability framing: "I believe this is the right call with roughly 70% confidence because X, and the 30% scenario where it goes wrong is Y." Fake precision \'97 presenting uncertain predictions as certain \'97 is an analytical failure.\
\
This framework is the operating system. Every analysis delivered in this project runs on these protocols, references these sources, applies these thresholds, and enforces these rules. It is a living document \'97 as new accuracy data accumulates on experts, as new metrics prove predictive, and as the roster and draft capital evolve, this framework should be updated accordingly.\
